JOHANNESBURG (miningweekly.com) &ndash; Mining activities at a section of TSX- and Aim-listed Caledonia Mining&rsquo;s Blanket mine, in Zimbabwe, resumed on Monday morning. All activities at the Eroica orebody, which contributed 10% of production in the first quarter, had been halted at the weekend, pending a full risk assessment and on site investigation into a fatal accident that occurred on May 12. &quot;[The fatality] is a serious setback in our efforts to continuously improve safety at Blanket mine. Our heartfelt condolences go out to the family, colleagues and friends of the deceased,&rdquo; said CEO Steve Curtis.